 is a key factor in the signal that we measure from biological tissue with nuclear magnetic resonance devices, such as MRI scanners. It is an essential tool for basic scientists developing new imaging techniques that target specific features of tissue microstructure. The system is widely regarded as the world-leading simulation of its kind and is now widely used as a validation tool for imaging scientists. We implemented it as part of the free and open-source Camino toolkit www.camino.org.uk. The actual page that documents its usage is http://cmic.cs.ucl.ac.uk/camino//index.php?n=Tutorials.MCSimulator.</gtr:description><gtr:id>4057EC66-E3A7-4180-B95D-E6AA3E86AE04</gtr:id><gtr:impact>A basic tool for development that underpins a range of cutting edge imaging techniques including ActiveAx, NODDI, and VERDICT.</gtr:impact><gtr:openSourceLicense>true</gtr:openSourceLicense><gtr:title>Camino Monte Carlo diffusion simulation</gtr:title><gtr:type>Software</gtr:type><gtr:url>http://cmic.cs.ucl.ac.uk/camino//index.php?n=Tutorials.MCSimulator</gtr:url><gtr:yearFirstProvided>2008</gtr:yearFirstProvided></gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutput></gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/F34ABF6D-D39C-4591-8DC2-F50DA6AC2885"><gtr:id>F34ABF6D-D39C-4591-8DC2-F50DA6AC2885</gtr:id><gtr:title>Information Processing in Medical Imaging</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/d58d9d7946ebcbf18bb4cbaf0e60ff2d"><gtr:id>d58d9d7946ebcbf18bb4cbaf0e60ff2d</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Clayden J</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2009-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:isbn>978-3-642-02497-9</gtr:isbn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/2DB0255F-F9F3-4B65-A78F-98A8594E7A16"><gtr:id>2DB0255F-F9F3-4B65-A78F-98A8594E7A16</gtr:id><gtr:title>Axon diameter mapping in crossing fibers with diffusion MRI.</gtr:title><gtr:paren